WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.161
( theme music playing )

01:53.240 --> 01:57.006
( woman pants )
BOY, THE AIR'S THINNER UP HERE
THAN I WOULD'VE THOUGHT.

01:57.110 --> 01:59.146
Sarah:
COME ON, FIONA,
YOU CAN DO IT!

01:59.250 --> 02:02.413
I CAN'T WAIT TO SHOW YOU
THE VIEW FROM THE TOP!

02:02.520 --> 02:05.341
YOU KNOW,
YOU WERE RIGHT.

02:05.450 --> 02:07.111
IT'S GOOD
THAT I GOT OUT.

02:07.220 --> 02:09.359
I THINK WAS GETTING
A LITTLE DEPRESSED INSIDE.

02:09.460 --> 02:11.826
JUST ME AND THE FUMES
FROM MY KILN

02:11.930 --> 02:14.319
AND THAT MOROSE N.P.R.

02:14.430 --> 02:15.852
- HERE.
- WHOO!

02:15.960 --> 02:18.064
TAKE THIS.
COME ON!

02:18.170 --> 02:19.933
- ALL RIGHT.
- ( hooting )

02:20.040 --> 02:24.500
JUST THROUGH HERE
YOU CAN SEE ALL THE WAY
TO THE OCEAN.

02:30.010 --> 02:31.705
BE CAREFUL UP AHEAD.

02:31.810 --> 02:35.678
- WHAT?
- WE'RE MOMENTS FROM
THE TOP, MERE MOMENTS.

02:35.780 --> 02:38.749
( panting )
I DIDN'T THINK
I WAS GONNA--

02:38.850 --> 02:40.556
MAKE IT.

02:42.790 --> 02:44.724
( gasps )

02:48.630 --> 02:50.427
FIONA?

02:57.270 --> 02:59.306
FIONA?

03:06.580 --> 03:09.219
- THIS TOP DOESN'T FIT.
- Anthony: HEE-YAH!

03:09.320 --> 03:12.517
IT'S THE RIGHT TOP,
IT'S THE WRONG CONTAINER.
PUT THE BROCCOLI IN A ZIPLOC.

03:12.620 --> 03:15.054
THEY'RE DIDN'T
EAT THE BROCCOLI
FROM YESTERDAY.

03:15.160 --> 03:17.048
- WHERE'S THE CARROTS?
- GET OFF OF ME!

03:17.160 --> 03:19.822
WHAT IS--
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:22.100 --> 03:23.465
JESUS.

03:23.570 --> 03:25.868
ALL RIGHT, IT'S TIME TO GO.
PUT YOUR JACKET ON.

03:25.970 --> 03:28.734
- I'M NOT PUTTING ON
THAT BUSTED OLD JACKET.
- YES, YOU ARE. WE JUST GOT IT!

03:28.840 --> 03:31.502
- NO, I'M NOT!
I'M GETTING MY OTHER ONE.
- YOU'RE NOT THE BOSS!

03:31.610 --> 03:33.805
- YOU WANT THAT ONE, GO GET IT!
- I DON'T KNOW WHERE IT IS!

03:33.910 --> 03:36.549
- WHERE DID YOU PUT IT?
- I DIDN'T PUT IT ANYWHERE!
IT'S YOUR JACKET!

03:36.650 --> 03:41.371
I'LL FIND THE OTHER JACKET.
JUST GO BRUSH YOUR TEETH,
YS.

03:41.480 --> 03:44.085
IT'S LIKE HE WANTS ME
TO LOSE MY TEMPER.

03:44.190 --> 03:45.748
NO KID WANTS THAT.
JUST GIVE HIM TIME.

03:45.850 --> 03:47.579
YOU'VE BEEN SAYING THAT
FOR TWO WEEKS.

03:47.690 --> 03:49.453
YOU HAVE TO REMEMBER
WHERE HE COMES FROM,

03:49.560 --> 03:51.448
WHAT THE SOCIAL WORKER
SAID ABOUT HIS MOTHER.

03:51.560 --> 03:54.051
MY SISTER'S A DRUG ADDICT.
TAYLOR NEVER ACT ED
LIKE THIS!

03:54.160 --> 03:55.559
- TAYLOR'S A GIRL.
- SO?

03:55.660 --> 03:58.322
SO SHE ISN'T HARDWIRED
TO BE AGGRESSIVE
AND TERRITORIAL.

03:58.430 --> 04:00.796
THAT'S THE REASON
SHE DOESN'T HAVE
THE SAME PROBLEM

04:00.900 --> 04:02.936
- WITH YOUR FATHER
THAT ECFIU DO.

04:03.040 --> 04:06.100
SO NOW EVERYTHING
THAT HAPPENED BETWEEN ME
AND MY FATHER IS MY FAULT?

04:06.210 --> 04:07.734
NO, I'M--

04:07.840 --> 04:09.137
IS YOUR BROTHER READY?

04:09.240 --> 04:11.344
HE WANTS TO KNOW
WHERE YOU PUT
HIS HAT.

04:11.450 --> 04:14.647
( sighs )
I'LL BE IN THE CAR.

04:15.850 --> 04:17.715
( sighs )

04:22.490 --> 04:25.084
Ruth:
WHY DO YOU NEED
MR. SIBLEY'S NAME?

04:25.190 --> 04:27.249
NO, MR. SIBLEY IS
RIGHT HERE.

04:27.360 --> 04:29.692
WHAT ARE THE LAST FOUR DIGS
OF YOUR SOCIAL?

04:29.800 --> 04:31.529
4281.

04:31.630 --> 04:33.131
4281.

04:33.240 --> 04:34.992
CORRECT.

04:35.100 --> 04:36.636
CORRECT.

04:36.740 --> 04:38.799
CORRECT.

04:38.910 --> 04:40.207
I'LL HOLD.

04:40.310 --> 04:42.107
ARE YOU LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING?

04:42.210 --> 04:43.370
YEAH, THE POTS AND PANS.

04:43.480 --> 04:46.040
OH, I MUST HAVE
FORGOTTEN THEM.

04:46.150 --> 04:47.913
WE CAN JUST
BUY NEW ONES.

04:48.020 --> 04:50.079
I CAN GO DOWN
TO CRATE & BARREL
RIGHT NOW.

04:50.190 --> 04:52.511
WE HAVE PRACTICALLY
A BRAND-NEW SET BACK
AT THE HOUSE.

04:52.620 --> 04:55.509
WELL, I DON'T WANT
TO RAID THEIR SUPPLY.

04:55.620 --> 04:57.554
BUT YOU LOVED
THAT CALPHALON.

04:57.660 --> 04:59.958
YOU RAVED ABOUT IT
WHEN WE GOT IT.

05:00.060 --> 05:03.291
THAT WAS BECAUSE IT
WAS MY FIRST EXPERIENCE
WITH ANODIZED ALUMINUM.

05:03.400 --> 05:05.459
WE DON'T NEED THOSE,
WE'LL BUY NEW ONES.

05:05.570 --> 05:07.834
IT'S AN INCREDIBLE
WASTE OF MONEY.

05:07.940 --> 05:08.861
I'M HERE.

05:08.970 --> 05:10.506
GOOD.

05:10.610 --> 05:13.374
AND YOU DO THE GAS
AS WELL? SPLENDID.

05:13.480 --> 05:15.801
NO, THANK YOU.

05:20.850 --> 05:24.115
DID YOU TALK TO DEAN HIKOLOS
ABOUT GOING BACK TO WORK?

05:24.220 --> 05:27.155
NO, I...
I DON'T WANT TO.

05:27.260 --> 05:28.557
I'M NOT ADY.

05:28.660 --> 05:31.424
IT'LL BE
THE SUMMER SESSION
IF AT ALL.

05:31.530 --> 05:33.794
I JUST THOUGHT YOU WERE
DOING SO MUCH BETTER.

05:33.900 --> 05:35.219
OH, I AM.

05:35.330 --> 05:37.218
AND I WANNA KEEP
DOING BETTER,

05:37.330 --> 05:41.130
WITHOUT ALL
THE STRESS AND STRAIN
OF TEACHING SCHOOL.

05:41.240 --> 05:43.959
WILL YOU LOOK AT THAT?

05:46.610 --> 05:49.579
REMEMBER WHEN
WE BOUGHT THIS?

05:49.680 --> 05:52.649
THAT'S WHEN YOU
ASKED ME TO MARRY YOU.

05:57.350 --> 06:00.956
OKAY, I'LL GO GET
OUR POTS AND PANS.

06:02.730 --> 06:05.119
I'LL BE BACK
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

06:05.230 --> 06:07.050
I'LL BE WAITING.

06:08.330 --> 06:10.560
( fake chuckle )

06:11.770 --> 06:14.739
( laughs )

06:14.840 --> 06:18.059
OKAY, YOU DID REALLY WELL
ON YOUR TYPING TEST.
GOT A 95.

06:18.170 --> 06:21.571
- THANKS.
- DON'T WORRY,
NO ONE EVER HAS GOTTEN 100.

06:21.680 --> 06:24.240
ONE PERSON DID,
BUT I THINK SHE WAS PSYCHIC.

06:24.350 --> 06:28.468
- OKAY, WE HAVE ONE DOWNTOWN--
- OH, I SHOULD PROBABLY
TELL YOU,

06:28.580 --> 06:31.447
I HAVE APPLIED FOR THIS GRANT
FOR EMERGING ARTISTS,

06:31.550 --> 06:33.711
AND IF I GET IT--
WHICH COULD BE THIS MONTH,

06:33.820 --> 06:36.823
OR EVEN THIS WEEK,
I'D HAVE TO STOP WORKING,
LIKE, IMMEDIATELY.

06:36.930 --> 06:39.228
YEAH WELL, "TEMP" IS SHORT
FOR TEMPORARY.

06:39.330 --> 06:40.991
OKAY, HERE WE ARE.

06:41.100 --> 06:43.819
"QUALITY CONTROL
AUDITING CLERK,
LEGAL DEPARTMENT,

06:43.930 --> 06:46.490
BRAEDEN CHEMICAL.
EMPLOYEE VERIFIES
ACCURACY OF FIGURES,

06:46.600 --> 06:48.795
BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS
RECORDED BY OTHER WORKERS,

06:48.900 --> 06:51.164
AS WELL AS
SUPPORT THE SUPPORT STAFF
IN GENERAL TASKS."

06:51.270 --> 06:53.170
- SOUND GOOD?
- OKAY.

06:53.280 --> 06:56.579
OKAY, LET ME CALL OVER THERE
AND SEE IF THEY'VE FOUND
ANYONE YET.

06:56.680 --> 06:58.477
IT'S A VERY
CONSERVATIVE COMPANY.

06:58.580 --> 07:00.548
YOU DO HAVE
CORPORATE ATTIRE, RIGHT?

07:00.650 --> 07:03.312
LIKE A BUSINESS SUIT?

07:03.420 --> 07:07.151
OR A NICE BLOUSE,
A SKIRT, SOME HOSE.

07:08.590 --> 07:10.820
Sarah:
I FEEL SO LUCKY.

07:10.930 --> 07:15.355
I AM JUST SO LUCKY
TO HAVE BEEN WITH HER
IN HER FINAL MOMENTS.

07:15.460 --> 07:17.826
WHAT A GIFT.

07:17.930 --> 07:19.363
SHE WAS SO ALIVE.

07:19.470 --> 07:22.337
AND SHE WAS HAPPY
HAPPY HAPPY,

07:22.440 --> 07:26.069
AND EXCITED
TO SEE THE VIEW.

07:26.170 --> 07:29.708
YOU'VE NEVER SEEN
SUCH A PERFECT MORNING
IN TOPANGA CANYON.

07:29.810 --> 07:32.347
WERE EITHER OF YOU OUT
THIS MORNING?

07:32.450 --> 07:35.214
- NO.
- OH.

07:35.320 --> 07:38.619
I CAN'T BELIEVE
FIONA'S GONE.

07:38.720 --> 07:43.020
- YOU KNEW HER TOO, HUH?
- YEAH, I DID.

07:43.130 --> 07:46.156
IT'S LIKE THE SECOND PERSON
YOU'VE KNOWN.

07:46.260 --> 07:47.955
Nate: I KNOW.

07:48.060 --> 07:51.097
THIS JUST MUST BE THE TIME
WHEN EVERYONE'S DYING.

07:51.200 --> 07:53.634
NATE, IT WAS
HER TIME.

07:53.740 --> 07:55.833
I WAS COMPELLED
TO BRING HER.

07:55.940 --> 07:58.408
I WAS DRIVING
THROUGH THE CANYON
TO GO ON MY HIKE

07:58.510 --> 08:00.831
AND MY CAR JUST PULLED OVER
INTO HER DRIVEWAY.

08:00.940 --> 08:02.168
WOW.

08:02.280 --> 08:06.717
IT'S LIKE SOMETHING SAID,
"BRING FIONA WITH YOU."

08:06.820 --> 08:09.584
THE SPIRIT
HAD TO HAVE HER.

08:12.250 --> 08:14.184
THE SPIRIT...

08:14.290 --> 08:17.327
WORKS IN MYSTERIOUS WAYS.

08:17.430 --> 08:19.898
( cell phone ringing )

08:24.230 --> 08:26.323
CORONER'S OFFICE.

08:26.430 --> 08:28.398
SHE MUST BE READY TO GO.

08:28.500 --> 08:30.400
AH...

08:30.510 --> 08:31.966
( chuckles )

08:34.480 --> 08:36.801
- YOU OKAY?
- YEAH.

08:36.910 --> 08:39.299
- WE'RE GONNA MAKE IT
BEAUTIFUL, RIGHT?
- YEP.

08:39.410 --> 08:41.446
( laughs )
YAY!

08:41.550 --> 08:44.644
I LOVE THESE FLOWERS.
( sniffs )

08:44.750 --> 08:45.910
OOH, THEY SMELL GOOD.
SMELL THEM.

08:46.020 --> 08:47.749
Woman:
IF YOU'RE UPSET, TELL HIM.

08:47.860 --> 08:50.624
IF HE LOVES YOU
HE SHOULD BE ABLE
TO HEAR THAT.

08:50.730 --> 08:52.755
I DON'T WANT
TO FREAK HIM OUT
UNNECESSARILY.

08:52.860 --> 08:56.296
- I THOUGHT BILLY WAS
BACK ON HIS MEDICATION.
- AH, THAT'S WHAT HE SAYS.

08:56.400 --> 08:59.938
"I'M BACK ON MY MEDS,"
LIKE THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.
"IS HE ON OR IS HE OFF?"

09:00.040 --> 09:03.532
HE'S COMPLETELY OBLIVIOUS
TO THE FACT THAT WE'RE ALL
JUST EXHAUSTED.

09:03.640 --> 09:07.076
THEY SHOULD CALL IT
"BIPOLAR ASSHOLE DISORDER."

09:07.180 --> 09:10.104
JUST TELL HIM. OKAY?
YOU NEED A BREAK.

09:10.210 --> 09:11.609
( sighs )

09:11.710 --> 09:14.270
YEAH, THAT SCARES ME TOO.

09:14.380 --> 09:16.610
I FEEL LIKE I HAVE
TO KEEP HIM CLOSE

09:16.720 --> 09:19.757
SO THAT IF HE FALLS OFF
THE EDGE SOMEONE WILL KNOW.

09:23.060 --> 09:26.120
PEOPLE ARE STARTING
TO NOTICE I'M PREGNANT.

09:27.300 --> 09:30.463
BRENDA,
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

09:30.570 --> 09:32.788
- OKAY, LIKE A GLOWING MOMMY.
- THANK YOU.

09:32.900 --> 09:34.993
REALLY.

09:35.100 --> 09:37.762
LOOK, YOU'VE GOT ONE
AT HOME AND ONE IN THERE,

09:37.870 --> 09:40.737
YOU KNOW, PUT YO ENERGY
WHERE IT DESERVES TO BE.

09:40.840 --> 09:44.139
- BILLY CAN TAKE CARE
OF HIMSELF.
- YEAH.

09:44.250 --> 09:47.014
YEAH, I KNOW.

09:47.120 --> 09:48.610
OKAY.

09:49.480 --> 09:51.345
Vanessa:
YOU LOOK HOT.

09:51.450 --> 09:54.988
I OUGHT TO LOOK FUCKING HOT.
I'VE BEEN STARVING MYSELF
LIKE A REFUGEE.

09:55.090 --> 09:57.149
-(laughs)
- ( television playing )

09:57.260 --> 09:59.694
OH, YOU'RE FUNNY.

09:59.800 --> 10:02.496
I COULD'VE DONE
THAT JOKE BETTER.

10:02.600 --> 10:06.058
( groans ) I GO'I'I'A
TO GO TO THE AIRPORT SOON
AND PICK UP THE BABYSI'I'I'ER.

10:06.170 --> 10:09.662
- AU PAIR.
- OKAY, THAT WORD IS
SO "BOUGIE." PLEASE.

10:09.770 --> 10:11.658
OKAY, NAN NY,
WHATEVER.

10:11.770 --> 10:14.034
THIS IS L.A.
EVERYBODY HAS
LIVE-IN HELP.

10:14.140 --> 10:15.437
I DON'T KNOW.

10:15.540 --> 10:18.805
ARE YOU MAD--
I MEAN, THAT I CAN'T HELP
YOU AS MUCH ANYMORE?

10:18.910 --> 10:20.946
- TELL ME.
- DON'T.

10:21.050 --> 10:23.245
EVERYTHING YOU EVER
WANTED IS COMING TRUE.

10:23.350 --> 10:26.148
IT'S JUST A STUPID SITCOM.
I'M SURE IT WILL GET
CANCELED.

10:26.250 --> 10:28.309
I JUST-- I DON'T WANT IT
TO BE WEIRD FOR YOU,

10:28.420 --> 10:31.389
YOU KNOW, HAVING A STRANGER
IN THE HOUSE, ESPECIALLY
FROM SASKATCHEWAN.

10:31.490 --> 10:35.620
- WHERE THE HELL
IS SASKATCHEWAN?
- NEAR CALGARY, I THINK.

10:35.730 --> 10:37.721
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH--

10:37.830 --> 10:40.537
SHE CAN HAVE HORNS
AND WEIGH 300 LBS.
FOR ALL I CARE.

10:40.640 --> 10:44.167
AS LONG AS SHE BRINGS IN
THE WATER BOTTLES, CAN BE HERE
WHEN THE CABLE GUY COMES

10:44.270 --> 10:46.500
AND STARTS PUTTING AWAY
THE GROCERIES THAT
ARE MELTING

10:46.610 --> 10:50.102
WHILE I'M GETTING
THE REST OUT OF THE CAR.
I JUST NEED ANOTHER ADULT.

10:51.850 --> 10:54.148
( Sarah sobbing )

11:03.430 --> 11:05.125
SARAH?

11:08.230 --> 11:12.394
OH, RUTHY, YOU NEVER GONNA
BELIEVE WHAT HAPPENED.

11:12.500 --> 11:15.333
FIONA'S DEAD.

11:15.440 --> 11:17.908
- FIONA?
- CLIMBING.

11:18.010 --> 11:21.832
I KNOW YOU HATED HER
FOR WHAT SHE DID TO NATE.

11:21.940 --> 11:24.374
BUT WE'VE LOST HER, RUTHY.

11:24.480 --> 11:26.072
SHE'S GONE.

11:26.180 --> 11:28.319
( sobbing )

11:33.660 --> 11:37.221
- I KNOW, IT'S HORRENDOUS.
- George: Jesus,
I can't imagine.

11:37.330 --> 11:39.890
- THERE WAS NOTHING
SHE COULD DO?
- No, nothing.

11:40.000 --> 11:42.389
FELL HUNDREDS OF FEET RIGHT DOWN
TO THE BOTTOM OF THE RAVINE,

11:42.500 --> 11:45.867
AND WAS DEAD
WHEN THEY PULLED HER OUT.
I'M JUST SICK ABOUT IT.

11:45.970 --> 11:48.939
FIONA WAS A VERY CLOSE
FRIEND OF MINE.
VERY CLOSE.

11:49.040 --> 11:51.201
You sure you don't need me
to come over there?

11:51.310 --> 11:53.801
I THINK SARAH'S IN SHOCK.

11:53.910 --> 11:56.071
IT'S NOT A PRETTY SCENE
DOWN HERE...

11:56.180 --> 11:59.547
ONLY APPROPRIATE
FOR FAMILY-- OF ORIGIN.

11:59.650 --> 12:03.381
PEOPLE--
I NEED PEOPLE.
WHO CAN WE CALL?

12:03.490 --> 12:06.141
- WHAT DID SHE SAY?
- SHE'S JUST JABBERING.
SHE'S INCOHERENT.

12:06.250 --> 12:10.084
- Keep me posted.
- OKAY. BYE.

12:10.190 --> 12:13.899
GET ME MY PHONE BOOK.
IT'S IN MY SATCHEL.

12:14.000 --> 12:17.766
I NEED
TO CIRCLE THE WAGONS.

12:21.270 --> 12:24.307
David:
DO I NEED TO COME DOWN THERE?

12:24.410 --> 12:27.971
OKAY OKAY, I'LL STOP BY
THE OFFICE WHEN I COME
TO PICK THE BOYS UP.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.729
BYE.

12:29.850 --> 12:32.478
DURRELL PULLED
A FIRE ALARM.

12:32.580 --> 12:36.311
NOW I HAVE
TO MAKE AN APPOINTMENT
WITH THE PRINCIPAL.

12:36.420 --> 12:38.547
I CAN'T TELL KEITH.

12:38.650 --> 12:42.450
HE'S JUST LOOKING
FOR MORE PROOF THESE KIDS
ARE TOO MESSED UP FOR US.

12:42.560 --> 12:45.358
- THE FOSTER'S
JUST TEMPORARY, RIGHT?
- NO, NOT REALLY.

12:45.460 --> 12:49.294
THEY TRY TO GET THEM
IN THE RIGHT PLACE, HAVE IT
LEAD TO ACTUAL ADOPTION.

12:49.400 --> 12:50.560
THAT'S THE IDEAL.

12:50.670 --> 12:52.399
- YOU WANT TO KEEP THEM?
- ( SlghS )

12:52.500 --> 12:54.058
I DO.

12:54.170 --> 12:57.606
ANTHONY'S SO CUTE
I'D KEEP HIM IN A HEARTBEAT.

12:57.710 --> 13:00.031
DURRELL, ON THE OTHER HAND,
IS A MESS.

13:00.140 --> 13:02.779
BUT WHAT CAN YOU EXPECT?
THESE KIDS COME FROM
A BROKEN HOME.

13:02.880 --> 13:06.202
THEIR DAD BASICALLY
ABANDONED THEM.

13:06.310 --> 13:08.471
SORRY.

13:08.580 --> 13:11.743
IT'S OKAY.

13:11.850 --> 13:13.886
HEY, DID I TELL YOU
I FOUND MY OWN PLACE?

13:13.990 --> 13:16.515
A TWO BEDROOM.
I'M WAITING TO HEAR.

13:16.620 --> 13:18.485
THEN MY BOYS CAN STAY OVER.

13:18.590 --> 13:22.094
I CAN'T WAIT
TO WAKE UP WITH THEM AGAIN.
THAT'S WHAT I MISS.

13:22.200 --> 13:26.523
PAJAMAS, AND MESSY HAIR
AND THEIR EYES ALL SLEEPY.

13:27.700 --> 13:29.839
WELL, I HOPE YOU
GET THE PLACE,

13:29.940 --> 13:32.306
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

13:32.410 --> 13:34.401
WHAT I WANT...

13:34.510 --> 13:36.637
IS TO BE BACK HOME.

13:36.740 --> 13:38.901
BUT I HAVE
TO TAKE IN THE REALITY

13:39.010 --> 13:41.547
THAT IT'S NOT
GOING TO HAPPEN.

13:44.820 --> 13:48.984
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE MESS.
I WAS RUSHING AROUND
THIS MORNING.

13:49.090 --> 13:50.853
I DIDN'T GET A CHANCE
TO PICK UP.

13:50.960 --> 13:54.589
YOU CERTAINLY DON'T
HAVE TO CLEAN FOR ME.
THAT'S WHAT I'M HERE FOR.

13:54.700 --> 13:56.691
I'M SO EXCITED.
I LOVE CALIFORNIA.

13:56.800 --> 13:59.564
- I PRACTICALLY
BARFED ON THE PLANE.
- WELL, DON'T DO THAT.

13:59.670 --> 14:02.639
- Julio: CAN SHE
COME IN MY ROOM?
- YEAH, HOLD ON, JULIO.

14:02.740 --> 14:04.537
UH, SO I WROTE UP A LIST.

14:04.640 --> 14:08.076
SOME OF IT IS COMMON SENSE--
DO THE DISHES WHEN THEY
START PILING UP.

14:08.180 --> 14:11.001
AND IF YOU COULD BE HERE
TOMORROW BETWEEN 10:00
AND 2:00,

14:11.110 --> 14:13.977
THE CABLE GUY'S COMING
'CAUSE OUR SATELLITE'S OUT.

14:14.080 --> 14:16.173
OH, DO YOU HAVE THOSE GIANT
WATER BOTTLES IN CANADA?

14:16.280 --> 14:18.441
- YEAH.
- THEY'RE WAY
TOO HEAW FOR ME.

14:18.550 --> 14:21.110
SO IF YOU EVER SEE THAT
IT'S EMPTY, GO AHEAD
AND BRING ONE IN.

14:21.220 --> 14:22.448
OH, OKAY.

14:22.560 --> 14:26.087
UM, WOULD IT BE OKAY
IF I GOT A LITTLE
SETTLED IN FIRST?

14:26.190 --> 14:28.522
OH MY GOD.
OF COURSE.

14:28.630 --> 14:30.359
- I'M SORRY. I'M--
- OH!

14:30.470 --> 14:34.190
- --JUST REALLY
HAPPY YOU'RE HERE.
- HELP IS ON THE WAY.

14:35.840 --> 14:39.936
OH, HERE'S THE E-MAIL
THAT'S FROM FIONA'S
ARTIST WEEK GROUP.

14:40.040 --> 14:42.008
MM, I'LL CALL THEM
FROM MY HOUSE.

14:42.110 --> 14:44.078
SHOULD WE REGROUP
IN THE MORNING?

14:44.180 --> 14:46.774
SURE.
I'M GOING TO STAY HERE
TONIGHT.

14:46.880 --> 14:48.814
GEORGE AND I ARE
IN TRANSITION MODE.

14:48.920 --> 14:51.946
YOU SOUNDED LIKE
YOU WERE TOGETHER
WHEN YOU WERE ON THE PHONE.

14:52.050 --> 14:55.087
YOU THREW THE BUM OUT
BECAUSE HE COULDN'T GET
