INSANE RIGHT NOW.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.366
Durrell:
LET GO OF THE DOOR
OR I'LL TELL D.C.F.S.!

27:56.470 --> 27:59.359
YOU THINK ANYBODY
OVER THERE GIVE A SHIT
ABOUT YOU?

27:59.470 --> 28:02.371
( boys grunt)

28:02.480 --> 28:04.300
YOU DID THAT TO YOURSELVES!

28:05.910 --> 28:07.400
( breathing heavily)

28:09.380 --> 28:12.281
( "You Light Up My Life"
Muzak playing )

28:22.500 --> 28:24.695
( humming to Muzak)

28:25.730 --> 28:29.769
* ADRIFT ON THE WATER

28:29.870 --> 28:33.909
* COULD IT BE ACTUALLY

28:34.010 --> 28:37.400
* WEARING THESE CLOTHES

28:37.510 --> 28:41.571
* I'VE NEVER BEEN

28:41.680 --> 28:45.389
* THIS FUCKING UNCOMFORTABLE

28:45.490 --> 28:48.812
* NEVER AGAIN

28:48.920 --> 28:54.051
* TO WEAR PANTYHOSE...

28:54.160 --> 29:00.395
* 'CAUSE YOU RIDE UP
MY THIGHS *

29:00.500 --> 29:03.958
* YOU'RE TIGHT ON MY ASS

29:04.070 --> 29:07.779
* YOU CLIMB UP MY CROTCH

29:07.880 --> 29:11.873
* YOU RUIN MY DAY

29:11.980 --> 29:16.041
* AND FILL MY SOUL

29:16.150 --> 29:19.938
* YOU FILL MY SOUL
WITH HATE *

29:20.050 --> 29:23.508
* IT CAN'T BE RIGHT

29:23.620 --> 29:29.627
* WHEN THEY FEEL SO TIGHT...

29:29.730 --> 29:30.754
* WHOO

29:30.870 --> 29:33.168
* 'CAUSE YOU AND YOU AND YOU

29:33.270 --> 29:35.397
- * ALL OF YOU...
- CLAIRE?

29:35.500 --> 29:38.537
* RIDE UP MY THIGHS.

29:38.640 --> 29:40.505
CLAIRE?

29:40.610 --> 29:44.376
IS MY MUSIC TOO LOUD?
DO YOU NEED ME
TO TURN IT DOWN?

29:44.480 --> 29:48.177
- OH, YEAH,
MAYBE A LITTLE. THANKS.
- ( Muzak ends)

29:50.120 --> 29:52.418
- ( doorbell rings )
- COMING!

29:56.590 --> 29:58.455
- HI, DADDY.
- SWEETHEART.

29:58.560 --> 30:00.027
OH, BOY.

30:00.130 --> 30:02.291
- HERE.
HAPPY HOUSEWARMING.
- OOH, BEAUTIFUL.

30:02.400 --> 30:04.368
( clinking )

30:05.330 --> 30:07.696
TEA'S READY!

30:07.800 --> 30:10.291
WHERE DOES RUTH KEEP
HER HAND LOTION?

30:10.400 --> 30:11.628
I DON'T KNOW.

30:11.740 --> 30:13.332
IT'S BEEN SO DRY
OUT THIS WEEK,

30:13.440 --> 30:15.874
AND THE ONLY STUFF IN
THE BATHROOM'S YOURS.

30:15.980 --> 30:18.198
MAYBE SHE TOOK IT
WITH HER.

30:22.020 --> 30:24.341
- TOOK IT WHERE?
- EARL GREY OR GREEN?

30:24.450 --> 30:26.918
- WHEN DID YOU MOVE IN?
- TWO DAYS AGO.

30:27.020 --> 30:29.557
STOP BEING SO NOSY.
EARL GREY OR GREEN?

30:29.660 --> 30:32.481
DADDY, I'M NOT,
I JUST--

30:32.590 --> 30:34.353
GREEN.

30:35.730 --> 30:37.152
SO I GUESS...

30:37.260 --> 30:40.718
YOU GUYS ARE JUST
TAKING YOUR TIME
UNPACKING?

30:40.830 --> 30:42.388
MM-HMM.

30:44.070 --> 30:49.098
LOOK, I RELY
ON RUTH TO TAKE CARE
OF YOU, DADDY.

30:50.910 --> 30:52.673
JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING.

30:52.780 --> 30:54.975
WE'RE FINE.

30:55.080 --> 30:59.619
THE ONLY REASON I'M ALONE IS
THAT RUTH'S SISTER WAS INVOLVED
IN A FATAL ACCIDENT.

30:59.720 --> 31:01.119
- OH, YOU'RE KIDDING.
- MM.

31:01.220 --> 31:03.108
EVIDENTLY, SHE'S BEING
BLAMED FOR IT.

31:03.220 --> 31:07.327
AND RUTH,
CARETAKER THAT SHE IS,
IS BY HER SIDE.

31:07.430 --> 31:10.354
APPARENTLY
SHE'S QUITE DISTRAUGHT.

31:10.460 --> 31:13.099
( women laughing )

31:13.200 --> 31:15.088
I THINK THEY'VE OUTLIVED
THEIR USEFULNESS.

31:15.200 --> 31:16.929
- MEN ARE OBSOLETE.
- Woman: IT'S TRUE.

31:17.040 --> 31:20.168
I FEEL MORE OF A CONNECTION
TO MY WOMEN FRIENDS THAN
ANY OF MY HUSBANDS.

31:20.270 --> 31:23.137
I'VE WANTED TO HAVE
AN ALL-WOMEN WEEKEND
ON MY LAND.

31:23.240 --> 31:25.049
- ( women gasp )
- NICE IDEA.

31:25.150 --> 31:27.243
LET'S MAKE IT
AN ALL-WOMAN YEAR!

31:27.350 --> 31:30.376
ALL WOMEN FOREVER!
A LAND OF NO MEN!

31:30.480 --> 31:33.210
( laughter, cheering )

31:33.320 --> 31:35.959
MEN CAN VISIT,
BUT ONLY FOR A WEEKEND.

31:36.060 --> 31:38.028
JUST TO SATISFY OUR NEEDS.

31:38.130 --> 31:40.257
BUT THEY HAVE TO BRING MONEY.

31:40.360 --> 31:43.921
I'VE GOT THE LAND, LADIES.
THERE'S 20 ACRES UP THERE
I DON'T USE AT ALL.

31:44.030 --> 31:46.521
WE'LL BUY YURTS
OFF THE INTERNET.

31:46.630 --> 31:47.767
SAVE ME A YURT.

31:47.870 --> 31:50.737
BRENDA, WE COULD MIDWIFE
YOUR BABY FOR YOU.

31:50.840 --> 31:52.762
YOU CAN DELIVER HER
IN A HORSE TROUGH.

31:52.870 --> 31:55.179
AND WE CAMP WHILE
YOU'RE IN LABOR.
MMM.

31:55.280 --> 31:56.907
I KNOW HOW TO GROW
VEGETABLES!

31:57.010 --> 31:58.739
WE'LL ONLYAT WHAT
I CAN GROW OR KILL.

32:02.920 --> 32:04.547
- NO MEN!
- ( screams )

32:04.650 --> 32:07.710
- NO MEN!
- ( laughing )

32:07.820 --> 32:10.482
I'M JUST HERE
TO PICK UP MY KID.

32:10.590 --> 32:13.024
THAT'S IT!
WE'LL USE THE MEN
FOR CHILD CARE,

32:13.130 --> 32:15.655
LIKE THEY'VE DONE TO US
FOR A GAZILLION YEARS.

32:15.760 --> 32:18.797
I'M MOVING IN
TO AN ALL-GIRL COMMUNE.
DON'T WORRY,

32:18.900 --> 32:20.458
I'LL SNEAK YOU IN
WHEN THEY'RE ASLEEP.

32:20.570 --> 32:23.368
- OKAY. UP UP UP.
- YEAH, DO YOU MIND
IF I STAY?

32:23.470 --> 32:25.506
- THIS IS KIND OF COOL.
- SURE. NO PROBLEM.

32:25.610 --> 32:27.760
Brenda:
BYE-BYE!

32:27.870 --> 32:29.178
- BYE!
- Bettina: BYE.

32:29.280 --> 32:30.304
BYE.

32:30.410 --> 32:32.640
- BYE, BEAUTIFUL.
- HAVE FUN, EVERYBODY.

32:36.250 --> 32:38.946
OKAY, WHO'S GOT WEED?

32:39.050 --> 32:40.779
Brenda: NOT ME.

32:40.890 --> 32:42.858
MINE'S ALL GONE.

32:42.960 --> 32:45.622
I THINK I KNOW WHERE
I'VE GOT SOME.

32:56.900 --> 32:58.299
I'M DONE.

32:58.410 --> 33:02.471
- WITH YOUR FLOSSING OR--?
- WITH THE KIDS.

33:02.580 --> 33:05.208
KEITH, IT'S NOT LIKE
THEY'RE SLIPPERS YOU CAN

33:05.310 --> 33:08.074
RETURN TO NEIMAN MARCUS
BECAUSE THEY DON'T FIT.

33:08.180 --> 33:10.114
THAT'S THE WHOLE POINT
OF FOSTER--

33:10.220 --> 33:12.279
SO YOU CAN SEE
WHETHER OR NOT IT WORKS.

33:12.390 --> 33:14.187
THAT'S WHAT
THE SOCIAL WORKER SAID.

33:14.290 --> 33:16.155
AND THIS IS DEFINITELY
NOT WORKING.

33:16.260 --> 33:18.251
- WE'RE JUST GEN15TING STARTED.

33:18.360 --> 33:20.885
IT'S BEEN TWO WEEKS.
THAT'S MORE THAN ENOUGH TIME
TO KNOW.

33:20.990 --> 33:22.992
WE SHOULD STOP
BEFORE THEY BOND TO US.

33:23.100 --> 33:24.590
BUT I'VE ALREADY
BONDED TO THEM.

33:24.700 --> 33:27.260
WHAT YOU'VE BONDED TO
IS THE IDEA OF BECOMING
YOUR MOTHER--

33:27.370 --> 33:29.429
JUST RUNNING AROUND HERE
BLIND TO EVERYTHING.

33:29.540 --> 33:32.304
- "OH, EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OKAY."
- SHH!

33:32.410 --> 33:35.129
AND YOU TURN INTO YOUR FATHER--
SOLVE EVERYTHING WITH A BEATING?

33:35.240 --> 33:37.379
- I HAVEN'T
TOUCHED THOSE KIDS!
- YOU WERE CLOSE.

33:37.480 --> 33:40.449
EXACTLY. THAT'S WHY
WHEN THE SOCIAL WORKER
COMES TOMORROW

33:40.550 --> 33:43.144
I'LL BE EXPLAINING TO HER
THAT THIS IS A BAD MATCH.

33:43.250 --> 33:46.686
- ( groans )
- YOU SHOULD PACK THEIR THINGS
IN THE MORNING.

33:50.090 --> 33:51.728
HOW CAN YOU
JUST ABANDON THEM

33:51.830 --> 33:55.027
WHEN THEIR LITTLE LIVES
HAVE ALREADY BEEN FILLED
WITH SO MUCH TRAUMA?

33:55.130 --> 33:57.928
GOOD,
SO NOW YOU ABANDON ME?

33:58.030 --> 34:00.169
THAT SOLVES EVERYTHING.

34:00.830 --> 34:02.798
( sighs )

34:02.900 --> 34:05.164
( lullaby playing )

34:08.810 --> 34:10.471
( cell phone ringing )

34:14.780 --> 34:16.418
( whispers )
HELLO?

34:16.520 --> 34:17.669
HEY, IT'S MAGGIE.

34:17.780 --> 34:19.509
Hey.

34:19.620 --> 34:22.009
I WAS JUST PUTTING
MAYA TO SLEEP.

34:22.120 --> 34:24.008
Have you seen
your mother?

34:24.130 --> 34:27.486
UM, WHY DO YOU ASK?

34:27.590 --> 34:31.265
WELL, I WAS
JUST OVER AT MY DAD'S,
AND SHE WASN'T THERE.

34:31.370 --> 34:34.589
AND THEN I TRIED
TO REACH HER AT THE HOUSE
AND NOBODY ANSWERED.

34:35.670 --> 34:37.262
HUH.
WELL, I, UM...

34:37.370 --> 34:40.203
Nate, we don't know
each other very well,

34:40.310 --> 34:43.074
BUT DO SOMETHING
FOR ME, WOULD YOU?

34:43.180 --> 34:45.842
AND I'LL MAKE
THE SAME PROMISE TO YOU.

34:46.910 --> 34:49.447
NEVER LIE TO ME.

34:49.550 --> 34:51.381
Okay?

34:54.960 --> 34:57.212
OKAY.

34:57.960 --> 34:59.552
SHE'S AT THE HOUSE.

34:59.660 --> 35:03.926
UM, IT'S JUST A BUNCH OF WOMEN.
THEY'RE HAVING A LITTLE PARTY.

35:04.030 --> 35:05.998
BUT SHE'S FINE.

35:06.100 --> 35:09.888
If there's a problem
with your dad, she didn't
tell me about it.

35:10.000 --> 35:12.230
OKAY.

35:14.070 --> 35:16.129
AND, UH...

35:16.240 --> 35:18.071
YOU KNOW,
BRENDA'S OVER THERE TOO.

35:18.180 --> 35:20.341
IT'S JUST ME AND MAYA HERE.

35:24.850 --> 35:27.512
UM, ARE YOU OKAY?

35:29.490 --> 35:31.958
I'M FINE.

35:32.060 --> 35:35.359
I'LL SEE YOU SOON
I HOPE. BYE.

35:43.640 --> 35:45.608
OH, HELLO, HONEY.

35:45.710 --> 35:49.339
( giggles )
TAKE OFF YOUR BUSINESS CLOTHES
AND COME JOIN US.

35:49.440 --> 35:54.070
SARAH MADE DINNER,
AND BETTINA'S IN RARE FORM.

35:54.180 --> 35:56.910
AND DOMINIQUE BROUGHT
SUSIE BRIGHT.

35:57.020 --> 35:59.341
DO YOU KNOW WHO SHE IS?

35:59.450 --> 36:01.452
NO.

36:02.490 --> 36:06.187
OH, THE WOMEN THOUGHT
SOME MARIJUANA

36:06.290 --> 36:09.054
MIGHT EASE THE PAIN
OF THE LOSS.

36:09.160 --> 36:11.219
I GUESS YOU FOUND IT.

36:11.330 --> 36:14.094
THIS SEEMS VERY BROWN.

36:14.200 --> 36:18.159
IS IT THE SAME STRENGTH
AS THE GREEN STUFF WITH
THE PUNGENT AROMA?

36:34.020 --> 36:36.284
DO YOU GUYS HAVE PAPERS?

36:36.390 --> 36:39.553
UH, THEY WERE ACTUALLY
HOPING FOR A BONG.

36:46.570 --> 36:48.936
YOU KNOW YOU HAVE TO PUT
WATER IN THAT, RIGHT?

36:49.040 --> 36:51.463
BETTINA KNOWS.

36:53.840 --> 36:56.536
OH, HONEY.

36:56.640 --> 36:58.449
WHAT?

36:59.750 --> 37:02.776
I DON'T HATE YOU.

37:04.590 --> 37:07.150
I DON'T HATE YOU
EITHER, MOM.

37:07.250 --> 37:09.480
YOU'RE JUST
SO MUCH LIKE ME.

37:09.590 --> 37:13.128
AND I SEE YOU
DOING THESE THINGS AND I FEEL
LIKE I'M SEEING MYSELF.

37:13.230 --> 37:15.551
WELL, I'M NOT
THAT MUCH LIKE YOU.

37:16.730 --> 37:19.392
IF YOU GIVE UP YOUR DREAMS
AND IT'S MY FAULT,

37:19.500 --> 37:21.297
I'LL NEVER FORGIVE MYSELF.

37:21.400 --> 37:23.539
NO, YOU WERE RIGHT.

37:23.640 --> 37:25.835
I MEAN, I HAVE TO BE ABLE
TO SUPPORT MYSELF.

37:25.940 --> 37:28.977
AND SOON AS THIS GRANT
COMES THROUGH I WILL.

37:29.080 --> 37:31.207
I MEAN, THIS JOB IS
JUST FOR NOW.

37:31.310 --> 37:33.141
PROMISE ME...

37:33.250 --> 37:36.276
PROMISE ME YOU'LL BE
WHO YOU WANNA BE.

37:46.460 --> 37:51.090
OH, I LOVE YOU,
SWEETHEART.

37:51.200 --> 37:53.725
I LOVE YOU TOO, MOM.

37:58.070 --> 38:00.607
YOU LOOK SO CORPORATE.

38:00.710 --> 38:02.075
( giggles )

38:02.180 --> 38:04.398
YOU LOOK
SO NOT CORPORATE.

38:04.510 --> 38:07.001
WON'T YOU COME DOWN
AND JOIN US?

38:07.110 --> 38:10.568
I CAN'T.
AS SOON AS I GET
THIS HOT-DOG SUIT OFF

38:10.680 --> 38:12.648
I AM GONNA TAKE A BATH
AND BE NAKED.

38:12.750 --> 38:16.413
IF I PUT ANYTHING ELSE ON
WITH A WAISTBAND
I'M GONNA CRY.

38:16.520 --> 38:19.023
I'LL KEEP MY FINGERS
CROSSED ANYWAY.

38:19.130 --> 38:20.779
( groans )

38:23.630 --> 38:26.895
Lederhosen
are trousers.

38:27.000 --> 38:29.468
Ah.

38:29.570 --> 38:31.936
But German for song
is lieder.

38:32.040 --> 38:35.339
Lieder.
Yes, correct.

38:35.440 --> 38:37.078
( knocking at door)

38:43.180 --> 38:46.718
HEY.

38:46.820 --> 38:50.051
Woman: _
Is there something
you wanted?

38:53.030 --> 38:56.227
Billy:
MAYBE IT'S TRUE THAT IT WASN'T
CLAIRE THAT I LOVED SO MUCH--

38:56.330 --> 39:01.358
BUT I LOVED HOW IT FELT
TO SEE THE WORLD WITH
ANOTHER PERSON...

39:02.400 --> 39:04.539
TO BE THE TWO OF US.

39:06.310 --> 39:08.801
I FELT LIKE SHE WAS
MY FIRST REAL LOVE.

39:08.910 --> 39:11.549
- ( TV turns off)
- I KNOW SHE'S JUST A KID,

39:11.650 --> 39:14.676
BUT WE WERE KIDS TOGETHER.

39:15.780 --> 39:17.645
( sighs )

39:20.650 --> 39:24.188
MY FIRST LOVE JUST DIED.

39:24.290 --> 39:26.281
SERIOUSLY?

39:26.390 --> 39:29.097
YEAH.
I WAS 15 WHEN I MET HER.

39:30.330 --> 39:33.493
SHE WAS 32.

39:33.600 --> 39:36.694
- WHOA.
- YEAH, OH, YEAH.

39:36.800 --> 39:40.031
EVERYONE AFTERWARDS
GOT ALL EXCITED, YOU KNOW--

39:40.140 --> 39:42.074
"WHAT DID SHE DO TO YOU?"

39:43.580 --> 39:45.901
EVERYBODY ALWAYS THOUGHT
SHE DID SOMETHING TO ME.

39:51.550 --> 39:53.586
YOU KNOW,
UP UNTIL FIONA

39:53.690 --> 39:57.148
I HAD JUST BEEN FOOLING AROUND
WITH GIRLS MY OWN AGE--

39:57.260 --> 40:02.596
DARK-ROOM-TRYING-TO-GET-
MY-HAN D-DOWN-SOM E-GIRL'S- PANTS
BU LLSHIT.

40:03.700 --> 40:06.897
FIONA LET ME
SEE ALL OF HER.

40:08.600 --> 40:10.898
AND I JUST LOVED HER.

40:14.210 --> 40:17.600
AND THAT WHOLE YEAR
I WAS SEEING OTHER GIRLS,
BUT I'M JUST-- I'M...

40:17.710 --> 40:20.645
( laughs )
YOU KNOW, I WROTE HER LETTERS.

40:21.920 --> 40:23.979
SOME OF THEM RHYMED.

40:27.720 --> 40:30.883
NOW I KNOW SHE PROBABLY LAUGHED
WHEN SHE READ THOSE LETTERS.

40:31.560 --> 40:34.120
I DOUBT SHE LAUGHED.

40:34.230 --> 40:37.859
WELL, YOU KNOW,
LOVE ISN'T SOMETHING YOU FEEL,
IT'S SOMETHING YOU DO.

40:37.960 --> 40:40.997
IF THE PERSON YOU'RE WITH
DOESN'T WANT IT, YOU KNOW,

40:41.100 --> 40:45.969
DO YOURSELF A FAVOR
AND SAVE IT FOR SOMEONE
WHO DOES.

40:51.310 --> 40:54.108
Bettina:
ARE YOU SURE IT'S OKAY
FOR US TO BE DOWN HERE, FISHER?

40:54.210 --> 40:56.747
Ruth:
OF COURSE I'M SURE.

40:56.850 --> 41:00.741
WE'VE ALL BEEN CONDITIONED
NOT TO TOUCH THE DEAD.

41:00.850 --> 41:04.388
- BUT IT'S OKAY.
- Bettina: OH, FIONA.

41:04.490 --> 41:07.721
YOU LOOK GOOD, BABE.

41:19.540 --> 41:22.930
I LOVE YOU.

41:23.040 --> 41:26.498
I FORGIVE YOU, FIONA,
FOR DEFLOWERING MY BOY.

41:26.610 --> 41:29.249
Brenda:
OH, SHE'S THE ONE.

41:29.350 --> 41:31.409
HE WAS ONLY 15.

41:31.520 --> 41:34.114
I KNOW, NATE TOLD ME.

41:34.220 --> 41:35.551
Ruth:
IT'S OKAY.

41:35.660 --> 41:37.651
HE WAS OKAY.

41:38.590 --> 41:41.184
OH, THANK YOU.

