( music fades )

44:08.840 --> 44:12.344
OH, THANK GOD,
THE CALIFORNIA ARTS
COMMISSION.

44:12.450 --> 44:14.600
- YES!
- YOU LOOK NICE.

44:14.720 --> 44:16.017
YOU MUST
BE JOKING.

44:16.120 --> 44:20.147
IT'S SEXY,
LIKE A BUSINESS LADY.

44:27.530 --> 44:30.055
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
HONEY?

44:30.160 --> 44:32.469
I JUST GOT REJECTED
FOR MY GRANT.

44:32.570 --> 44:34.891
THOSE DICKS.
LET ME SEE THAT.

44:37.740 --> 44:41.130
OH, WELL,
THERE WILL BE ANOTHER ONE.

44:41.240 --> 44:43.128
SHIT!

44:44.510 --> 44:47.502
MAYBE YOU'RE NOT
AN ARTIST.

44:47.610 --> 44:49.771
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

44:49.880 --> 44:52.883
DID IT HURT YOUR FEELINGS
WHEN I SAID IT?

44:52.990 --> 44:55.413
( sighs )
WELL, YEAH.

44:55.520 --> 44:57.579
MAYBE I'M RIGHT.

44:57.690 --> 45:01.558
MAYBE IF YOU WERE
AN ARTIST, YOU'D HAVE LAUGHED
WHEN I SAID THAT.

45:01.660 --> 45:03.196
LIKE, IF YOU TOLD ME
I WAS PURPLE

45:03.300 --> 45:07.088
I WOULD LAUGH BECAUSE
I KNOW I'M NOT PURPLE.

45:07.200 --> 45:09.395
BUT WHEN I SAID YOU WEREN'T
AN ARTIST, YOU FELT BAD

45:09.500 --> 45:12.663
MAYBE BECAUSE THERE'S
A GRAIN OF TRUTH IN IT.

45:12.770 --> 45:14.499
( sighs )

45:14.610 --> 45:18.774
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO
TOOK ME BY MY SHOULDERS
AND LOOKED ME IN MY EYES

45:18.880 --> 45:21.371
AND TOLD ME THAT I WAS
AN ARTIST.

45:21.480 --> 45:22.970
MAYBE YOU WERE.

45:23.080 --> 45:26.015
MAYBE ARE.
MAYBE YOU AREN'T.
I DON'T KNOW.

45:28.220 --> 45:31.383
NO ONE ELSE CAN
TELL ANYONE WHAT TO DO,

45:31.490 --> 45:33.856
LEAST OF ALL ME.

45:36.830 --> 45:38.866
THAT'S THE GOOD NEWS.

45:40.670 --> 45:44.538
- ( door opens )
- Vanessa: DONNA, ARE YOU--
( gasps )

45:44.640 --> 45:47.404
HELLO.
HOW DO YOU DO?

45:47.510 --> 45:49.330
WHO ARE YOU?

45:49.440 --> 45:51.806
THAT'S MR. CLARINGTON.

45:54.310 --> 45:56.346
WHO IS HE?

45:56.450 --> 45:59.510
OH, HE'S HOMELESS.
I WAS COMING OUT
OF THE TRADER JOE'S

45:59.620 --> 46:02.555
AND HE WAS HUNGRY
SO I WAS JUST GOING
TO MAKE HIM SOME PANCAKES.

46:02.660 --> 46:04.184
I KNOW IT'S NOT
A GREAT MEAL, BUT--

46:04.290 --> 46:06.554
- WHERE ARE THE BOYS?
- THEY'RE AT SCHOOL.

46:06.660 --> 46:08.924
DONNA...

46:09.030 --> 46:13.091
YOU CANNOT BRING
STRANGE PEOPLE HOME.
THIS ISN'T CANADA!

46:13.200 --> 46:15.168
I WASN'T TRYING
TO CAUSE ANY TROUBLE.

46:15.270 --> 46:17.898
BUT THANK YOU BOTH KINDLY
FOR YOUR HOSPITALITY.

46:18.000 --> 46:21.333
- NEVER EVER COME BACK HERE!
- OH MY GOD, THAT'S SO MEAN.

46:21.440 --> 46:23.908
- I'M SO SORRY,
MR. CLARINGTON.
- YOU'RE FIRED, DONNA.

46:24.010 --> 46:28.003
I'M CALLING THE AGENCY
AND I'M TELLING THEM YOU'RE
OUT OF YOUR FUCKING MIND!

46:28.110 --> 46:29.316
I NEEDED SOMEONE TO HELP ME,

46:29.420 --> 46:31.843
NOT SHOOT VIDEOS
OF THEMSELVES DANCING

46:31.950 --> 46:34.145
AND INVITE THE HOMELESS IN
FOR PANCAKE BREAKFAST.

46:34.250 --> 46:36.787
GO PACK YOUR STUFF.
I NEED YOU TO LEAVE NOW.

46:36.890 --> 46:39.085
I HAVE NOWHERE TO GO.

46:39.190 --> 46:42.023
I DON'T CARE.
FIND SOMEWHERE TO GO!

46:42.130 --> 46:44.155
FINE.

46:45.730 --> 46:50.360
IF I GET SOMETHING
FROM "SURVIVOR," CAN YOU
FORWARD IT TO ME?

46:50.470 --> 46:52.438
YES.

46:53.640 --> 46:55.528
OKAY.

47:00.710 --> 47:03.975
( knocking at door)

47:04.080 --> 47:06.685
- PUNK.
- WAIT ONE SECOND
BEFORE YOU OPEN THAT!

47:06.790 --> 47:10.317
- David: GUYS.
- THE RESTRAINING ORDER
WENT OUT ON FRIDAY.

47:10.420 --> 47:13.321
- Anthony: YOU'RE WEAKER.
- Durrell: YOU'RE WEAKEST!

47:13.430 --> 47:15.694
I'M TRAINED IN HANDLING
PSYCHOTIC BREAKS.

47:15.800 --> 47:18.621
BOYS, WE HAVE COMPANY!

47:18.730 --> 47:20.322
WELL, IT SOUNDS LIKE
A SHITSTORM,

47:20.430 --> 47:22.068
BUT I DON'T HAVE A CLUE
HOW I CAN HELP YOU.

47:22.170 --> 47:24.491
- Anthony: OW! I HATE YOU.
- OKAY, LATER. BYE.

47:24.600 --> 47:26.431
SORRY.
EVERYTHING'S
FALLING APART.

47:26.540 --> 47:29.634
- MUST BE THE MOON.
- YEAH, EXACTLY, WE HAVE
THE SAME SITUATION HERE.

47:29.740 --> 47:31.139
THE BOYS ARE NOT
DOING WELL.

47:31.240 --> 47:32.969
- NOT AT ALL.
- ( cell phone ringing )

47:33.080 --> 47:34.911
I-- GO AHEAD,
I WILL LET IT RING.

47:35.020 --> 47:37.238
- TELL ME HOW IT'S BEEN.
- WE HAVE A REAL PROBLEM HERE.

47:37.350 --> 47:40.080
OR NOT!
WE'RE NOT SURE EXACTLY.

47:40.190 --> 47:43.353
WHAT WE NEED
IS YOUR INPUT,

47:43.460 --> 47:46.657
YOUR FEEDBACK.
PERHAPS THE BEST WAY
TO HANDLE THIS--

47:46.760 --> 47:48.648
I AM SO SORRY.
I DO HAVE TO TAKE THIS.

47:48.760 --> 47:52.127
- Anthony: GIRL!
- NO. I'M ALMOST
OUT OF HERE.

47:52.230 --> 47:54.562
HOLD ON ONE SECOND.
OKAY...

47:54.670 --> 47:59.061
- UH, THAT'LL BE IT THEN?
- LISTEN, I DON'T THINK THINGS
ARE WORKING OUT FOR THE KIDS.

47:59.170 --> 48:02.003
I MEAN, I'M NOT SURE
WE'RE THE RIGHT MATCH.

48:06.150 --> 48:10.109
YOU HAVE NO IDEA THE HELL
I HAVE PULLED CHILDREN OUT OF.

48:10.220 --> 48:13.144
I MEAN, HOUSES FILLED
TO THE BRIM WITH GARBAGE,
CAT FECES.

48:13.250 --> 48:15.889
YOU ARE DOING FINE
IN MY BOOK.

48:15.990 --> 48:17.810
I HAVE NEVER SEEN
THESE BOYS DOING BETTER.

48:17.920 --> 48:19.979
- THEY'RE FLOURISHING.
- "FLOURISHING"?

48:20.090 --> 48:22.593
GOOD.
YES, THAT'S WHAT
I THOUGHT. THANK YOU.

48:22.700 --> 48:25.567
- WE'RE THRILLED
TO HAVE THEM HERE.
- OKAY. GREAT. YEAH--

48:25.670 --> 48:28.093
- LISTEN, COULD YOU JUST
STAY FIV'IugINU-I—ES?

48:28.200 --> 48:30.998
- WAIT. SHE NEEDS TO GO.
- I'VE GOTTA GO.

48:31.100 --> 48:32.806
YEAH, I'M ON MY WAY.

48:32.910 --> 48:35.128
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
WITH TRAFFIC...

48:37.910 --> 48:39.707
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU
JUST DID THAT.

48:39.810 --> 48:42.517
YOU KNOW, DAVID,
JUST PRETENDING THAT
SOMETHING IS WORKING

48:42.620 --> 48:46.044
- DOESN'T MEAN
IT'S ACTUALLY WORKING.
- ( David sighs )

48:46.150 --> 48:51.554
DON'T WORRY, GUYS.
EVERYTHING'S GONNA
BE OKAY.

48:51.660 --> 48:53.685
Kirsten:
HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM PERSONNEL YET?

48:53.790 --> 48:55.451
I STARTED OUT
AS A TEMP TOO.

48:55.560 --> 48:58.552
IF YOU HAVE HALF A BRAIN
THEY'LL OFFER YOU
SOMETHING PERMANENT.

48:58.660 --> 49:01.561
DID YOU GET MY PRESENT?

49:01.670 --> 49:04.639
OH, THE E-CARD
WITH THE DAYI\IIE(SI;ING PUPPIES?

49:04.740 --> 49:06.901
IT WAS VERY CUTE.
THANK YOU.

49:07.010 --> 49:08.204
YEAH, BABY.

49:08.310 --> 49:10.733
NO, I MEANT
MY OLD BATHROOM PASS.

49:10.840 --> 49:13.047
IF PERSONNEL CALLS,
WHICH I HEARD
COULD HAPPEN,

49:13.150 --> 49:16.449
THEY'LL GIVE YOU YOUR OWN,
BUT IN THE MEANTIME YOU CAN
USE MY OLD MY ONE.

49:16.550 --> 49:18.370
I'M TELLING
OPERATIONS.

49:18.480 --> 49:21.119
REALLY,
YOU CAN HAVE IT,
CLAIRE.

49:27.590 --> 49:29.126
THANK YOU.

49:29.230 --> 49:32.529
YOU'RE GONNA
LOVE IT HERE, CLAIRE.
YOU REALLY ARE.

49:37.200 --> 49:40.431
- ( New Age music playing )
- ( cell phone ringing )

49:42.440 --> 49:44.328
HELLO?

49:46.880 --> 49:48.142
YEAH.

49:48.250 --> 49:51.947
YEAH YEAH,
I CAN DEFINITELY
PICK UP THE KIDS.

49:52.050 --> 49:54.541
OH, OKAY.
OKAY. GOOD GOOD.

49:54.650 --> 49:56.459
SEE YOU THEN.
BYE-BYE.

50:04.200 --> 50:07.067
I'M GONNA TAKE FIONA
TO THE CREMATORIUM.

50:07.170 --> 50:10.333
HOW NICE OF YOU.
I'M SURE SHE'LL
APPRECIATE THAT.

50:15.540 --> 50:17.405
HAVE YOU SEEN SARAH?

50:17.510 --> 50:20.104
OH, SHE ALREADY LEFT.
SHE WAS CANOODLING
IN THE BACK ROW,

50:20.210 --> 50:22.314
- FOUND AN OLD BOYFRIEND
I THINK.
- SHE LEFT?

50:22.420 --> 50:24.877
- ARE YOU GOING THEN?
- GOING WHERE?

50:24.980 --> 50:27.312
UP TO TOPANGA.
SHALL WE MEET THERE?

50:28.620 --> 50:31.885
AREN'T WE ALL GOING OUT
TO THE HOME AND...

50:31.990 --> 50:33.878
- COMMUNE...
- (chuckles)

50:33.990 --> 50:35.651
WEEKEND?

50:35.760 --> 50:37.591
OH.

50:37.700 --> 50:40.225
WE WERE JOKING.

50:43.740 --> 50:45.139
( sighs )

50:45.240 --> 50:48.732
( doorbell rings )

50:48.840 --> 50:52.071
HEY, GUYS!
GO PUT YOUR BOOKS
IN YOUR ROOMS

50:52.180 --> 50:54.375
AND GET READY FOR YOUR BATH.

50:57.820 --> 51:00.084
YOU WANNA MOVE BACK IN?

51:02.020 --> 51:03.715
EXCUSE ME?

51:03.820 --> 51:07.426
YEAH, I'VE BEEN THINKING
A LOT ABOUT IT AND I GUESS
YOU WERE RIGHT.

51:07.530 --> 51:10.192
UM, IT'S NOT GOOD FOR THE BOYS.
THEY NEED YOU HERE.

51:12.970 --> 51:14.699
WOW.

51:14.800 --> 51:16.392
YEAH.

51:16.500 --> 51:19.799
THANK YOU SO MUCH,
VANESSA.

51:19.910 --> 51:22.777
YEAH.
SO, I'M STARTING DINNER.

51:22.880 --> 51:28.000
WHY DON'T YOU GO DO
THEIR BATHS AND WE CAN EAT
IN ABOUT 20 MINUTES?

51:28.110 --> 51:31.773
LET ME, UH, TAKE THIS
TO THE KITCHEN FIRST.

51:31.880 --> 51:33.689
MM.

51:52.440 --> 51:54.362
OH.

51:54.470 --> 51:55.903
HELLO.

51:56.010 --> 51:58.604
I BROUGHT
THE POTS AND PANS.

52:00.050 --> 52:03.349
THAT-- THAT WASN'T
NECESSARY.

52:03.450 --> 52:06.385
ON SECOND THOUGHT,
YOUR OTHER IDEA WAS
THE BETTER ONE.

52:06.490 --> 52:10.551
I WENT DOWN
TO CRATE & BARREL AND
BOUGHT MYSELF ANOTHER SET.

52:10.660 --> 52:12.821
YOU DID?

52:12.930 --> 52:15.751
I KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON, RUTH.

52:15.860 --> 52:18.021
YOU DO?

52:18.130 --> 52:20.928
YES, I DO.
NONE OF YOUR FURNITURE
IS HERE.

52:21.030 --> 52:22.566
YOU ONLY BROUGHT ONE
CHANGE OF CLOTHING.

52:22.670 --> 52:25.366
- NO TOILETRIES.
- I BROUGHT MY SOAP.

52:25.470 --> 52:28.633
OH NO, PLEASE, LOOK--

52:28.740 --> 52:31.800
LET'S NOT WASTE ANY MORE
OF EACH OTHER'S TIME, OKAY?

52:31.910 --> 52:35.004
IT'S NOT RESPECT FUL.
I GET IT.

52:35.110 --> 52:38.079
YOU WANT TO LEAVE ME.

52:38.180 --> 52:41.183
BUT FIRST YOU WANT
TO MAKE SURE THAT I HAVE
EVERYTHING THAT I NEED,

52:41.290 --> 52:43.315
WHICH IS...

52:43.420 --> 52:46.753
VERY KIND AND THOUGHTFUL
AS YOU ALWAYS ARE.

52:46.860 --> 52:48.350
GEORGE, IT'S NOT BECAUSE--

52:48.460 --> 52:51.623
IT DOESN'T MATTER WHY.
IT'S OKAY.

52:51.730 --> 52:54.290
I CALLED THE DEAN.

52:54.400 --> 52:56.095
I START BACK
THIS SEMESTER.

52:56.200 --> 52:59.909
AND THANKS TO YOU
I HAVE MY APARTMENT...

53:00.010 --> 53:02.604
AND MY POTS...

53:02.710 --> 53:04.769
AND MY PANS.

53:04.880 --> 53:07.371
SO THANK YOU.

53:10.950 --> 53:13.487
I LOVED YOU.

53:15.090 --> 53:18.116
YOU LOVED ME.

53:18.220 --> 53:20.780
THAT WAS A GOOD THING.

53:22.160 --> 53:24.822
NOW IT'S CHANGED.

53:27.200 --> 53:29.430
SO...

53:30.970 --> 53:33.530
CONSIDER YOURSELF FREE.

53:42.210 --> 53:44.542
( pots clang )

53:54.730 --> 53:59.394
* ON EVERY DAY
YOU GAZE UPON THE SUNSET *

53:59.500 --> 54:03.732
* WITH SUCH LOVE
AND INTENSITY *

54:05.410 --> 54:07.401
* WHY...

54:07.510 --> 54:10.206
* IT'S, UH, IT'S ALMOST

54:10.310 --> 54:13.404
* AS IF YOU COULD
ONLY CRACK THE CODE *

54:13.510 --> 54:16.343
* THEN YOU'D
FINALLY UNDERSTAND *

54:16.450 --> 54:21.945
* WHAT THIS ALL MEANS

54:22.050 --> 54:26.419
* AH, BUT IF YOU COULD,
DO YOU THINK YOU WOULD *

54:26.530 --> 54:28.782
* TRADE IT ALL?

54:28.890 --> 54:32.257
* ALL THE PAIN

54:32.370 --> 54:35.692
* AND SUFFERING

54:37.540 --> 54:39.508
* AH, BUT THEN YOU'D MISS

54:39.610 --> 54:44.900
* THE BEAUTY OF THE LIGHT
UPON THIS EARTH *

54:45.010 --> 54:50.846
* ANDD THE SWEETNESS
OF THE LEAVING. *
